-- WAZ Mediengruppe Sells Newspapers, Printing House in Bulgaria, Trud Says
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 2010-12-15T07:39:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/waz-sells-newspapers-printing-house-in-bulgaria-trud-says.html
WAZ Mediengruppe  sold its assets in
Bulgaria, including newspapers and a printing house, to Vienna-
registered BG Printinvest Ltd for an undisclosed price,  Trud 
reported, citing the company.  The transaction includes Trud and 24 Hour daily newspapers
and 168 Hours weekly newspaper, Trud said. The Bulgarian
partners of BG Printinvest include  Ognian Donev , chairman of
Sopharma, the biggest Bulgarian generic drugmaker, and Lyubomir
Parvlov, former chairman of the Sofia-based Municipal Bank.  The Essen, Germany-based publisher announced in August
plans to sell its operations in southeastern Europe.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Elizabeth Konstantinova  in Sofia at 
 ekonstantino@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  